THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 284 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto the
2 provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. In relation to positions in the unclassified service, each appointing
4 authority shall recruit, evaluate, select, manage and promote employees,
5 including, without limitation, through the making of any determination that
6 affects the pay of an employee, in a manner which recognizes relevant
7 employment experience obtained by an applicant or employee in the Federal
8 Government as equivalent to employment experience obtained in the government
9 of this State.
10 Sec. 3. 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, an appointing
11 authority shall not require an applicant for a position of employment in the
12 classified or unclassified service of the State to have obtained a bachelor’s degree
13 as a condition precedent to employment.
14 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply if the appointing authority
15 determines that the knowledge, skills or abilities required for the position for
16 which the applicant is applying may only be obtained through a course of study
17 in pursuit of and that culminates in the award of a bachelor’s degree.
18 Sec. 4. NRS 284.160 is hereby amended to read as follows:
19 284.160 1. The Administrator shall prepare, maintain and revise as
20 necessary a master classification plan for all positions in the classified service,
21 based upon similarity of duties and responsibilities, so that the same qualifications
22 may reasonably be required for, and the same schedule of pay may be equitably
23 applied to, all positions in the same class.
24 2. In determining the qualifications that may be reasonably required for all
25 positions in the same class pursuant to subsection 1, the Administrator shall
26 [periodically review each class of positions in the classified service which require a
27 person to hold a bachelor’s degree and, whenever the Administrator deems it
28 necessary for the efficiency of the public service, revise the qualifications to] allow
29 a person to substitute equivalent employment experience [or skills in lieu of a
30 bachelor’s degree.] obtained in the Federal Government for any employment
31 experience required to be obtained in the government of this State.
32 3. The Administrator shall review annually the classification plan of each
33 appointing authority using the audit function developed and implemented pursuant
34 to NRS 284.107.

