9 (a) The Administrator deems it necessary for the efficiency of the public
10 service;
11 (b) The change is not proposed in conjunction with an occupational study; and
12 (c) The Administrator, at least 20 working days before acting upon the
13 proposed change:
14 (1) Provides written notice of the proposal to each member of the
15 Commission, to all departments and to any head of an employees’ organization who
16 requests notice of such proposals; and
17 (2) Posts a written notice of the proposal in each of the principal offices of
18 the Division.
19  Any occupational study conducted by the Division in connection with the
20 preparation, maintenance or revision of the classification plan must be approved by
21 the Commission.
22 6. If no written objection to the proposed change to the classification plan is
23 received by the Administrator before the date it is scheduled to be acted upon, the
24 Administrator may effect the change. The Administrator shall report to the
25 Commission any change in the classification plan made without its approval at the
26 Commission’s next succeeding regular meeting.
27 7. If a written objection is received before the date the proposed change is
28 scheduled to be acted upon, the Administrator shall place the matter on the agenda
29 of the Commission for consideration at its next succeeding regular meeting.
30 Sec. 5. NRS 284.210 is hereby amended to read as follows:
31 284.210 In relation to positions in the classified service, each appointing
32 authority shall, consistent with the regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant
33 to NRS 284.205, recruit, evaluate, select, manage and promote employees ,
34 including, without limitation, through the making of any determination that
35 affects the pay of an employee:
36 1. Through open competition on the basis of knowledge, skills and ability
37 and without regard to an applicant’s or employee’s religious or political opinions or
38 affiliations, race, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age or
39 disability.
40 2. In a manner which recognizes relevant employment experience obtained
41 by an applicant or employee in the Federal Government as equivalent to
42 employment experience obtained in the government of this State.
43 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.

